labels.label:
This flow consumes CSV, JSON or AVRO data from a source 
Kafka topic, parses the data using a schema provided by the 
CDP Schema Registry and ingests it into an Iceberg table.

Define a KPI on this connection to monitor
failed write operations.

labels.label:
Parses S3 Trigger to retrieve bucket 
and key for new telemetry file

Retrieves the new Telemetry File 
that landed in S3 bucket

Sends events to two different 
folders in S3 bucket based on
routing rule configured.

Routes and Filters the events 
based on routing rules using SQL.

Mock Data for S3 Trigger to test locally 
before deploying as function.
 
After setting up S3 buckets and uploading
sample telemetry into bucket, right click
on processor and select 'Run Once'

The function that processing new telemetry data 
from an S3 bucket, does processing and sends
transformed data into different S3 folders

parameters.name: telemetry_inbound_endpoint_keystore_password
parameters.description: The password for the the keystore used to connect to the inbound gateway endpoint

parameters.name: telemetry_inbound_endpoint_truststore_password
parameters.description: The password for the the truststore used to connect to the inbound gateway endpoint

parameters.name: aws_access_key_password
parameters.description: AWS secret access key secret to fetch and write objects to S3

parameters.name: routing_rule_geo_event
parameters.description: The rule to filter and route for certain types of types of events

parameters.name: s3_region
parameters.description: The region where the bucket is located.

parameters.name: aws_access_key_id
parameters.description: AWS access key id to fetch and write objects to S3 bucket

parameters.name: routing_rule_speed_event
parameters.description: The rule to filter and route for certain types of types of events
parameters.value: SELECT * FROM FLOWFILE where eventSource = 'truck_speed_event' and speed > 40

parameters.name: s3_dest_path_speed_event
parameters.description: The S3 folder that certain filtered events will be written to.

parameters.name: s3_dest_path_geo_event
parameters.description: The S3 folder that certain filtered events will be written to.

parameters.name: s3_bucket
parameters.description: S3 bucket where telemetry data will be processed

parameters.name: CDP Workload User Password
parameters.description: Specify the password of the CDP machine user or workload user you're using to authenticate against Kafka and Hive.

parameters.name: Schema Registry Hostname
parameters.description: Specify the hostname of the Schema Registry you want to connect to. This must be the direct hostname of the Schema Registry itself, not the Knox Endpoint.

parameters.name: CDP Workload User
parameters.description: Specify the CDP machine user or workload user name that you want to use to authenticate to Kafka and Hive. Ensure this user has the appropriate access rights in Ranger for the Kafka topic and ID Broker for Hive access.

parameters.name: Iceberg Table Name
parameters.description: Specify the Iceberg table you want to write to running in your Hive Virtual Warehouse.

parameters.name: CSV Delimiter
parameters.description: If your source data is CSV, specify the delimiter here.

parameters.name: Data Input Format
parameters.description: Specify the format of your input data. You can use "CSV", "JSON" or "AVRO" with this ReadyFlow.

parameters.name: Kafka Consumer Group Id
parameters.description: The name of the consumer group used for the source topic you are consuming from.

parameters.name: Hive Catalog Namespace
parameters.description: Specify the Hive Catalog Namespace. The default value is default, which references the database catalog created automatically when you activate an environment in Cloudera Data Warehouse.

parameters.name: Kafka Broker Endpoint
parameters.description: Specify the Kafka bootstrap servers string as a comma separated list.

parameters.name: CDPEnvironment
parameters.description: The CDP Environment configuration resources

parameters.name: Schema Name
parameters.description: Specify the schema name to be looked up in the Schema Registry for the Source Kafka Topic

parameters.name: Kafka Source Topic
parameters.description: Specify a topic name that you want to read from.
